  "original_title": "Notification to Airtel subscribers who use only 2G, 3G enabled Mobile Phones",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Notification to Airtel subscribers who use only 2G, 3G enabled Mobile Phones",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Telecommunications Regulatory Commission of Sri Lanka (TRCSL) has granted permission to Bharti Airtel Lanka (Pvt) Ltd (Airtel) to shut down their 3G mobile network by June 24, 2022.",
        "While issuing a public notice, the TRCSL said with the sunset of the 3G network, the 3G connectivity of Airtel subscribers who use only 2G and 3G enabled mobile phones would be disconnected automatically after the scheduled date of network shut down.",
        "Airtel's 2G network will continue to operate normally, and voice and text message connectivity will be available to all 2G and 3G customers.",
        "The 3G shutdown is primarily intended to utilize the existing frequencies to deploy 4G services that offer better speed and capacity.",
        "A timeline of 15 months has been given to Airtel to avoid service disruptions that might be experienced at the end of the transition period due to the shutdown of their 3G network.",
        "Airtel is obliged to absorb at least 90% of its 3G subscriber base into its 4G network during the transition phase, subject to the following conditions.",
        "1. Conduct public awareness campaigns to encourage Airtel subscribers to migrate to the 4G network before the 3G network is decommissioned.",
        "2. Take every endeavour to provide 4G handsets for its 3G subscribers at subsidized rates on installment basis",
        "3. Drive the transition by offering incentives such as a series of different promotions, an impressive tariff package for the first six months.",
        "4. Notify its 3G subscribers via SMS at regular intervals to upgrade to 4G-enabled handsets before the deadline.",
        "If you are an Airtel subscriber who is still using a 2G or 3G enabled phone, you may contact Airtel over the short code 780 immediately to obtain the 4G connectivity together with a new mobile phone under concessionary terms.",
        "Please note that you will only be able to enjoy this concession until June 1, 2022.",
        "If you have encountered any difficulty in obtaining a 4G mobile phone during the said time limit, you may lodge a complaint with this Commission, the TRCSL Director General said. (Chaturanga Samarawickrama)"
      ],
